# Repo Laws

## Package manager lock
Never mix package managers. If AGENTS.md says yarn, use yarn. If npm, use npm. Never run the other one.

## No console.log in production code
Use the project's logger (see AGENTS.md for the import path). `console.log` is allowed in scripts and tests only.

## Non-zero exit on test failure
Every test command must produce a non-zero exit code when tests fail. Never swallow exits. Never claim "tests pass" without pasting the actual terminal output.

## Verification before completion
Before claiming any task complete:
1. Run the relevant test command.
2. Paste the actual output (not a summary).
3. Confirm exit code 0.

## Scope discipline
Implement what was asked. Do not refactor adjacent code. Do not add features not requested. Do not improve error handling in code you're not touching. One logical change per session.

